    <h1>20-Player UNO — Massive Multiplayer Card Games</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">Play UNO with up to 20 players in a single room. The biggest online UNO experience anywhere.</p>

    <h2>Why Play With 20 Players?</h2>
    <p>Most UNO games cap out at 10 players. We don't. Our engine supports up to 20 players in real-time, making it perfect for parties, classrooms, team events, and large friend groups. The chaos of a 20-player UNO game is an experience you won't forget.</p>

    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>Games with 11 or more players automatically use two full decks (220 cards), ensuring there are always enough cards to go around. The game engine handles shuffling, dealing, and deck replenishment seamlessly.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>2–10 players:</strong> Standard 110-card deck</li>
      <li><strong>11–20 players:</strong> Double 220-card deck</li>
      <li><strong>7 cards</strong> dealt to each player at the start</li>
      <li><strong>Auto-play</strong> keeps the game moving if someone is AFK</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Perfect For</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Party Nights</strong> — Get everyone in one room, no app downloads needed</li>
      <li><strong>Classrooms</strong> — Fun, family-friendly game for students</li>
      <li><strong>Office Events</strong> — Quick team-building game during breaks</li>
      <li><strong>Discord Communities</strong> — Share the invite link and play instantly</li>
      <li><strong>Family Gatherings</strong> — All ages can join from any device</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Works Everywhere</h2>
    <p>Every player can join from their own device — phone, tablet, laptop, or desktop. No installs, no accounts. Just share the room code or invite link and everyone is in the game within seconds.</p>

    <h2>Features</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Real-time gameplay with WebSocket technology</li>
      <li>Smart UI layout that scales for any number of players</li>
      <li>30-second turn timer with automatic AFK play</li>
      <li>Spectator mode for latecomers</li>
      <li>Host controls: kick players, toggle stacking, reorder seats</li>
      <li>Instant reconnection if you lose connection</li>
    </ul>

